com.mcc.ul
Class AoDevice

java.lang.Object
  com.mcc.ul.AoDevice

public class AoDevice
extends java.lang.Object

This class represents an analog output subsystem on a DAQ device. In addition to analog input methods, this class contains methods to access information and the configuration of the AO subsystem.

To create an instance of this class, call the getAoDev() method of the DaqDevice class.

highThreshold - High threshold of an analog trigger.
unit - The ThresholdUnit enumeration indicating the threshold unit.
retriggerCount - Number of samples to acquire during each trigger event when retrigger mode is enabled.
